{"id": 24, "date": "2024-06-03T15:14:42", "date_gmt": "2024-06-03T20:14:42", "guid": {"rendered": "https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/?page_id=24"}, "modified": "2024-06-24T14:26:01", "modified_gmt": "2024-06-24T19:26:01", "slug": "ua-code-of-student-conduct", "status": "publish", "type": "page", "link": "https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/what-is-hazing/ua-code-of-student-conduct/", "title": {"rendered": "GSU Code of Student Conduct"}, "content": {"rendered": "\n<p>The information below reflects the Office of Student Conduct as described on <a href=\"https://www.gram.edu/student-life/judicial-affairs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Grambling State University&rsquo;s Student Conduct (Judicial Affairs)</a> page. The official rules are published in the <a href=\"https://www.gram.edu/student-life/judicial-affairs/docs/Revised%20Code%20of%20Student%20Conduct%20Handbook.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Revised Code of Student Conduct handbook (PDF)</a>.</p>\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Purpose of the Office of Student Conduct</h2>\n\n<p>The purpose of the Office of Student Conduct is to ensure that students will not be deprived of life, liberty or property, administer a fair student disciplinary process that adheres to prescribed standards and to establish guidelines and rules to ensure that students maintain appropriate behavior at the University and off-campus. The Code of Student Conduct creates an expectation of behavior that the Institution deems acceptable. It is each student&rsquo;s responsibility to adhere to the policies and standards of conduct prescribed by the University, the Board of Supervisors for the University of Louisiana System, and applicable law.</p>\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Goals</h2>\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>To facilitate a process that promotes student development by challenging and supporting students owning individual responsibility;</li>\n<li>To use educational strategies and disciplinary counseling as catalysts for self-understanding and personal growth;</li>\n<li>To enforce a system characterized by accountability, compassion, and increased civility; and</li>\n<li>To promote a safe, orderly and positive University climate through informational programming, training, and intervention efforts.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Student conduct resources</h2>\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://cm.maxient.com/reportingform.php?GrambingStateUniv&amp;layout_id=0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Incident report form</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.gram.edu/student-life/judicial-affairs/docs/Revised%20Code%20of%20Student%20Conduct%20Handbook.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Student Code of Conduct (PDF handbook)</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Contact</h2>\n\n<p><strong>Office of Student Conduct</strong><br />\nGrambling State University<br />\n403 Main St, PO Box 4309<br />\nGrambling, LA 71245<br />\nPhone: <a href=\"tel:+13182747782\">(318) 274-7782</a><br />\nE-mail: <a href=\"mailto:turnert@gram.edu\">turnert@gram.edu</a></p>\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button has-custom-width wp-block-button__width-100\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link wp-element-button\" href=\"https://www.gram.edu/student-life/judicial-affairs/docs/Revised%20Code%20of%20Student%20Conduct%20Handbook.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">View revised Code of Student Conduct (PDF)</a></div>\n</div>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>The information below reflects the Office of Student Conduct as described on Grambling State University&#8217;s Student Conduct (Judicial Affairs) page. [&hellip;]</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 0, "parent": 17, "menu_order": 0, "comment_status": "closed", "ping_status": "closed", "template": "", "meta": {"hero_blocks": "", "sidebar_menu": "", "sidebar": false, "sidebar_type": "select", "hero": false, "title_alignment": "left", "title_width": "standard", "footnotes": ""}, "class_list": ["post-24", "page", "type-page", "status-publish", "hentry"], "_links": {"self": [{"href": "https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/pages/24", "targetHints": {"allow": ["GET"]}}], "collection": [{"href": "https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/pages"}], "about": [{"href": "https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/types/page"}], "author": [{"embeddable": true, "href": "https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/users/1"}], "replies": [{"embeddable": true, "href": "https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/comments?post=24"}], "version-history": [{"count": 9, "href": "https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/pages/24/revisions"}], "predecessor-version": [{"id": 407, "href": "https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/pages/24/revisions/407"}], "up": [{"embeddable": true, "href": "https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/pages/17"}], "wp:attachment": [{"href": "https://endhazing.sl.ua.edu/wp-json/wp/v2/media?parent=24"}], "curies": [{"name": "wp", "href": "https://api.w.org/{rel}", "templated": true}]}}